.TH RWRITE-AWAY 1 "Dec 12, 1994"

.SH NAME
.B rwrite-away
\- rwrite autoreply file maintainer

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rwrite-away
[\fIreason\fP|\fI-b\fP|\fI-q\fP]
.br

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Rwrite-away
makes automatically an rwrite autoreply file from your message
database or keyboard input.  \fBRwrite-away -b\fP removes the
autoreply file and \fBRwrite-away -q\fP queries the current away
status.

.SH AUTHOR
Timo J. Rinne <tri@cirion.fi>
.SH FILES
$HOME/.rwrite-away
.P
$HOME/.rwrite-autoreply

.SH SEE ALSO
rwrite(1), mkrwritebox(1), write(1), rwrited(8)
